President Joe Biden delivered a speech at the Salt Lake City VA to commemorate the one-year anniversary of the signing of the PACT Act, a significant law that provides assistance to veterans exposed to toxic materials. Biden emphasized the importance of caring for veterans and their families, highlighting the impact of burn pits on veterans' health. He urged veterans to enroll in VA healthcare, get screened for toxic exposure, and file claims for benefits. Biden also mentioned other initiatives aimed at supporting veterans, such as connecting them to job opportunities and addressing mental health issues. He concluded by emphasizing the need for unity and collaboration to fulfill the nation's obligations to its veterans.